Personal Introduction Program
Simple interactive Python program that demonstrates basic Input → Processing → Output (IPO) concepts.

Description
This program prompts the user for their name, age, and hobbies, then prints a friendly welcome message using formatted strings. It is designed for beginners learning how to handle input, store values, and display output in Python.

Files
Project_Personal_Introduction_Program.ipynb — Colab notebook (original code & outputs)
personal_introduction.py — (optional) standalone .py version for local use
screenshot.png — visual proof of a sample run

How to run
Option 1 — Google Colab

Click the "Open In Colab" badge above.
Run the notebook cells (Runtime → Run all).
Provide inputs when prompted.
Option 2 — Locally

Ensure Python 3.8+ is installed.
If you have personal_introduction.py, run:

  code:
python personal_introduction.py
Enter your name, age, and hobbies when prompted.

Code (core logic)
Extracted from the notebook for quick reference:
# Welcome banner
print("  Hellow world ! \n  My name Is MD AFROZ ANSARI \n \t Welcome to new world of coding in Data science ........")

# Gather inputs
name = input("What is your Name? \t")
age = input("What is your age ? \t")
Hobby = input("What are your Hobbies ? \t ")

# Output
print(f" Welcome {name} ! ")
print(f"You are {age} years old and love to {Hobby}")

Technical Details
Architecture: Linear flow (prompt → read → print)
Input handling: Tab character (\t) used in prompts for visual alignment
Variables: name (str), age (str), Hobby (str)
Formatting: f-strings used to create user-friendly messages
Error handling: Not included in the original notebook — consider adding validation (e.g., ensure age is numeric)
